1
00:00:35,590 --> 00:00:36,990
This day...

2
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:40,750
-our...
-our...

3
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:45,020
-dumbest face-off ever
-dumbest face-off ever

4
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,290
-began.
-began.

5
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:20,720
Shido!

6
00:01:25,620 --> 00:01:27,510
Shido.

7
00:01:31,220 --> 00:01:32,360
Hey, Shido.

8
00:01:33,100 --> 00:01:34,630
Looks like

9
00:01:34,660 --> 00:01:36,259
I'm the winner this quarter.

10
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:39,880
Yotsuya.

11
00:01:40,630 --> 00:01:44,280
You just got lucky this time.
Don't get full of yourself.

12
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:45,470
Why shouldn't I?

13
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:48,950
I'm the top performer in the Sales Dept.
this quarter, after all.

14
00:01:48,950 --> 00:01:52,509
Alright, alright.
Go back to Section 1 if you're done here.

15
00:01:52,530 --> 00:01:53,580
Well.

16
00:01:54,670 --> 00:01:57,140
By the way, what about your performance?

17
00:02:00,580 --> 00:02:03,310
You were bragging so much before.

18
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:05,410
Aren't you embarrassed?

19
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:07,780
But Mr. Shido is also
the No. 1 in our section.

20
00:02:07,780 --> 00:02:10,139
Stay out of this! What's your problem?

21
00:02:10,169 --> 00:02:11,530
Trying to start something?

22
00:02:11,530 --> 00:02:12,670
I'm not starting anything.

23
00:02:12,670 --> 00:02:14,960
I'm just stating the results
of our face-off.

24
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:15,950
Listen here,

25
00:02:15,970 --> 00:02:18,800
the project I'm working on
will get bigger and bigger soon.

26
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,660
Mr. Onishi!

27
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:23,060
This quarter is just as lively as well.

28
00:02:23,090 --> 00:02:24,620
You should get used to it too.

29
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:26,320
Get used to what?

30
00:02:26,350 --> 00:02:29,030
Their rivalry is legendary
in the Sales Dept.

31
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:32,040
This happens every time
the sales figures come out.

32
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:37,900
[Project Presentation]

33
00:02:36,660 --> 00:02:39,820
Though I did say you
should come up with more proposals...

34
00:02:39,820 --> 00:02:41,480
I came up with three more proposals

35
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:43,870
than this guy.

36
00:02:43,890 --> 00:02:46,100
Quality over quantity.

37
00:02:46,130 --> 00:02:48,490
Churning out useless proposals
is just wasted effort.

38
00:02:48,490 --> 00:02:52,100
You'd be better off preparing more material
instead of running your mouth.

39
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:55,380
The moment an opportunity appears,
they'll do anything to one-up each other.

40
00:02:55,380 --> 00:02:57,390
It's like that at work.

41
00:02:57,420 --> 00:02:59,040
Don't tell me you think that way.

42
00:02:58,710 --> 00:03:01,870
[98.976; Monthly Rank No.1]

43
00:03:01,220 --> 00:03:03,420
That's insane!

44
00:03:03,450 --> 00:03:04,780
They're like that in life as well.

45
00:03:04,780 --> 00:03:07,090
I can't believe you got 98.976 points!

46
00:03:07,110 --> 00:03:10,410
-That game at the welcome party too?
-Yeah.

47
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:13,040
Anyway, those two just can't stand losing.

48
00:03:14,350 --> 00:03:15,550
Huh? Where'd they go?

49
00:03:23,290 --> 00:03:24,880
Mr. Minami, sorry.

50
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:26,310
-Please be the judge for us.
-What?

51
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:27,910
Ah, please.

52
00:03:28,490 --> 00:03:30,250
Wait, what's going on?

53
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:33,680
That kind of thing happens all the time.
You'll get used to it.

54
00:03:34,820 --> 00:03:36,810
Ready... go!

55
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,870
Argh...

56
00:03:43,610 --> 00:03:44,850
Darn it...

57
00:03:48,660 --> 00:03:50,150
Ah!

58
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:53,760
So then,

59
00:03:53,790 --> 00:03:57,490
loser Shido, what should I make you do?

60
00:03:57,520 --> 00:04:00,130
I really hate the way you say that.

61
00:04:00,790 --> 00:04:04,820
They just can't resist
competing over anything.

62
00:04:07,890 --> 00:04:11,820
[Development]

63
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:11,990
I'll do my best to meet your expectations.

64
00:04:12,630 --> 00:04:15,690
I'll keep you updated on any progress.

65
00:04:16,230 --> 00:04:16,870
Okay.

66
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:19,120
If you have any other questions,

67
00:04:19,450 --> 00:04:21,180
please feel free to contact me anytime.

68
00:04:21,180 --> 00:04:21,630
Okay.

69
00:04:22,540 --> 00:04:24,130
Okay.

70
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:26,670
I look forward to
working with you going forward.

71
00:04:26,670 --> 00:04:28,080
That's all for today then.

72
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:29,000
Goodbye.

73
00:04:32,790 --> 00:04:33,550
Higashino.

74
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:34,500
Yes!

75
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:38,450
Sorry if that startled you earlier.

76
00:04:38,780 --> 00:04:39,990
Oh, no.

77
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:42,850
But... it was a bit surprising.

78
00:04:43,610 --> 00:04:46,920
Mr. Shido, you're usually
so cool and smart.

79
00:04:46,950 --> 00:04:47,900
Right!

80
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:52,240
But why does your IQ drop
the moment Mr. Yotsuya's around?

81
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,580
Whenever I see that guy,

82
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,650
I just lose my head.

83
00:04:56,740 --> 00:04:58,920
Come to think of it,
Yotsuya is from Section 1.

84
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:02,210
If you want to compete in sales results,
why not just compete within our section?

85
00:05:02,210 --> 00:05:04,740
I'm not trying to compete with everyone.

86
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:05,950
I just...

87
00:05:06,780 --> 00:05:08,710
don't want to lose to Yotsuya.

88
00:05:09,780 --> 00:05:11,850
Actually, I've always been curious—

89
00:05:12,350 --> 00:05:14,610
why are you so obsessed with beating him?

90
00:05:14,850 --> 00:05:18,240
Is there any other reason besides you
joining the company at the same time?

91
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:20,170
I have a twisted fate with that guy.

92
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:22,190
We've been rivals since high school.

93
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:24,190
-What?
-You two have such a history?

94
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:27,830
I know it's stupid to still be like this
once we're out in society.

95
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:31,060
But it's already become a habit.

96
00:05:31,260 --> 00:05:33,909
By the way, is there a penalty
for the loser?

97
00:06:09,990 --> 00:06:10,720
Oh.

98
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:12,420
You're here.

99
00:06:13,550 --> 00:06:15,680
You made me carry all this heavy stuff.

100
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:17,800
The winner...

101
00:06:19,850 --> 00:06:20,780
Makes the rules.

102
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:24,020
Alright. Come in.

103
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:27,980
Excuse me then.

104
00:06:31,540 --> 00:06:36,120
Then... to celebrate me
taking first place in sales,

105
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:38,680
cheers!

106
00:06:40,290 --> 00:06:42,220
Why am I celebrating your victory?

107
00:06:43,909 --> 00:06:45,750
You set the rules, huh?

108
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:48,430
The winner calls the shots.

109
00:06:48,830 --> 00:06:50,650
Give up and celebrate for me.

110
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:54,000
Then for our next face-off...

111
00:06:55,690 --> 00:06:57,950
whoever finishes the bottle first wins.

112
00:06:58,170 --> 00:06:59,400
Are you a kid?

113
00:07:00,540 --> 00:07:02,560
Afraid to lose, are you?

114
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,720
I'm in.

115
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:15,770
[Fake Fact Lips]

116
00:08:17,010 --> 00:08:21,070
[Episode 1: Whoever Makes the Other
Fall in Love First Wins!]

117
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:24,430
Alright, I win again.

118
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:29,190
My liver's been hardened
by years of client dinners.

119
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:31,440
Don't underestimate me.

120
00:08:31,460 --> 00:08:32,760
Same here.

121
00:08:33,059 --> 00:08:36,320
I just drank too much at a client dinner
with Sakuyo Foods yesterday.

122
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:39,150
So this round's a draw.

123
00:08:39,179 --> 00:08:40,870
Stop being childish.

124
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:43,650
You started it.

125
00:08:43,820 --> 00:08:46,680
-What? How am I being childish?
-Alright, alright.

126
00:08:47,380 --> 00:08:49,630
Let's have some water.

127
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:52,310
You're too naive, Ryo.

128
00:08:52,330 --> 00:08:53,600
Huh?

129
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:57,770
You think I'll just keep losing forever?
You couldn't be more wrong.

130
00:09:01,970 --> 00:09:03,600
[Business Card]

131
00:09:06,660 --> 00:09:10,370
[Kiritani Yuka]

132
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:08,250
Kiritani...

133
00:09:08,830 --> 00:09:11,440
That pretty girl
from the Secretarial Section?

134
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:14,740
She slipped this into my hand
this morning.

135
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,350
Don't be surprised yet.

136
00:09:17,380 --> 00:09:18,530
Flip it over.

137
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:19,620
[Kiritani Yuka]

138
00:09:20,010 --> 00:09:23,190
[Kirata-yu]

139
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:23,310
This is...

140
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:25,000
What should I do?

141
00:09:25,020 --> 00:09:29,440
The most unattainable woman in our company
actually asked me out in private.

142
00:09:31,660 --> 00:09:33,490
Well, that settles it.

143
00:09:40,210 --> 00:09:40,810
Ryo?

144
00:09:42,270 --> 00:09:42,760
What's wrong?

145
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:45,290
She has such terrible taste!

146
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,010
Huh?

147
00:09:46,030 --> 00:09:48,770
Miss Kiritani, I'm devastated.

148
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:51,900
Didn't expect you to be such
a shallow woman who only judges by looks.

149
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:53,920
Are you saying I'm just a pretty face
with no substance?

150
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:57,180
Isn't that the case with every woman
who's ever chased you?

151
00:09:57,550 --> 00:09:59,940
Yoshizawa,
in the first year of high school.

152
00:09:59,940 --> 00:10:02,140
Saki and Mitsu, in second year,
and Airi, in third year...

153
00:10:02,140 --> 00:10:04,350
Shut up!

154
00:10:04,370 --> 00:10:06,160
Why do you remember all that so clearly?

155
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:09,610
Because every time you started
dating someone, you'd come bragging to me,

156
00:10:09,610 --> 00:10:12,690
and when it ended,
you'd come whining to me.

157
00:10:13,330 --> 00:10:15,410
No. That's not true.

158
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:16,090
What?

159
00:10:16,830 --> 00:10:18,060
You're just bitter.

160
00:10:18,470 --> 00:10:19,860
Because I'm popular.

161
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:22,090
No.

162
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:26,140
No matter how good you are at work,
you're hopeless with women.

163
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:28,720
You've got some nerve saying that.

164
00:10:28,940 --> 00:10:31,190
Isn't it because you're always
chasing women

165
00:10:31,190 --> 00:10:32,940
that you can't beat me at work?

166
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:34,950
That was just this quarter.

167
00:10:34,980 --> 00:10:37,330
Who knows? You're already getting
carried away over a business card.

168
00:10:37,330 --> 00:10:39,680
I'm sure next quarter...

169
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:41,000
Anyway,

170
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:43,550
when it comes to popularity with women,
I win.

171
00:10:44,860 --> 00:10:47,710
Someone as haughty
and high-maintenance as you—

172
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:49,670
if you actually started dating,
your true colors would show soon enough.

173
00:10:49,670 --> 00:10:51,620
What?

174
00:10:51,650 --> 00:10:55,830
I'm clearly a reliable man
with professional dignity.

175
00:10:55,850 --> 00:10:58,120
And hate losing.

176
00:10:58,150 --> 00:11:01,740
Only men who crave victory have a future.

177
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,870
And most importantly...

178
00:11:04,970 --> 00:11:06,010
I'm handsome.

179
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:10,720
Eh? What?

180
00:11:11,180 --> 00:11:13,130
Nothing to say now, huh?

181
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:15,640
No, you've just left me speechless.

182
00:11:15,660 --> 00:11:17,510
Go ahead and admire it some more—

183
00:11:17,540 --> 00:11:20,900
this face of mine that charms all ages.

184
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:22,850
Stop being so full of yourself.

185
00:11:23,370 --> 00:11:28,030
Back in college, I even had a guy with
a girlfriend confess his feelings to me.

186
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:29,610
Ugh, that's gross!

187
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:31,320
Huh? Really?

188
00:11:31,860 --> 00:11:33,190
Hard to believe, right?

189
00:11:33,310 --> 00:11:37,070
But honestly, I'm probably on par with

190
00:11:37,090 --> 00:11:37,840
your exes, don't you think?

191
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:40,640
I can't believe
someone has such questionable taste.

192
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:43,970
Whatever you say now
just sounds like the whining of a loser.

193
00:11:45,980 --> 00:11:47,250
I'd

194
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:49,940
rather sleep with a woman

195
00:11:50,470 --> 00:11:53,000
I'm not even attracted to
than sleep with you.

196
00:11:53,190 --> 00:11:54,990
Huh? What are you talking about?

197
00:11:55,190 --> 00:11:57,300
Why do you just assume I'm the bottom?

198
00:11:57,330 --> 00:11:59,660
Because you said you could
hold your own against my ex-girlfriends.

199
00:11:59,660 --> 00:12:01,080
That's not what I meant.

200
00:12:01,650 --> 00:12:02,490
Besides,

201
00:12:02,510 --> 00:12:05,470
even if I were a woman,
there's no way I'd sleep with someone

202
00:12:05,470 --> 00:12:07,090
with skills as bad as yours.

203
00:12:07,740 --> 00:12:09,800
Like you'd even know.

204
00:12:09,830 --> 00:12:11,690
I don't need to see it to know.

205
00:12:12,050 --> 00:12:15,650
You're the one
who just relies on your looks

206
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:18,220
and lies there like a dead fish.

207
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:19,800
Huh? No way.

208
00:12:19,830 --> 00:12:21,690
Wait, doesn't that mean
you just admitted I'm handsome?

209
00:12:21,690 --> 00:12:23,440
Ah, nice attempt at changing the subject.

210
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:25,010
I hit the mark, didn't I?

211
00:12:25,030 --> 00:12:28,830
You're the one who only thinks about
yourself—probably a two-pump chump.

212
00:12:28,830 --> 00:12:32,410
What? You'd finish way faster! Wanna bet?

213
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:34,980
No, you'd be faster.

214
00:12:35,010 --> 00:12:36,680
Then let's have a face-off.

215
00:12:38,870 --> 00:12:39,720
What?

216
00:12:40,490 --> 00:12:44,150
Then let's see who can hold out longer—
dare?

217
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:46,920
Stop talking nonsense, you drunk!

218
00:12:46,940 --> 00:12:50,570
What? Running away?

219
00:12:50,590 --> 00:12:52,490
Alright, alright.

220
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:54,710
I don't even need to compete to know.

221
00:12:54,730 --> 00:12:56,250
You...

222
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:57,130
Zen.

223
00:12:58,260 --> 00:12:59,100
What?

224
00:13:01,460 --> 00:13:03,920
You're the one
who suggested this face-off.

225
00:13:04,260 --> 00:13:05,500
Don't regret it.

226
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:11,120
Bring it on.

227
00:13:16,930 --> 00:13:19,080
Then, let's start in three minutes.

228
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:22,430
Use whatever you like best as your "fuel."

229
00:13:23,330 --> 00:13:25,860
Whoever finishes
has to admit it on their own.

230
00:13:26,130 --> 00:13:27,150
No cheating.

231
00:13:27,610 --> 00:13:28,740
Where are you going?

232
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:29,890
Toilet.

233
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:33,020
What?

234
00:13:41,910 --> 00:13:44,050
That wouldn't be fair.

235
00:14:03,230 --> 00:14:04,190
Hey.

236
00:14:05,290 --> 00:14:07,660
You haven't stopped, have you?

237
00:14:07,790 --> 00:14:08,900
No.

238
00:14:09,700 --> 00:14:11,060
This is so weird.

239
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,460
What's even going on here?

240
00:14:13,830 --> 00:14:15,760
It's a face-off.

241
00:14:15,970 --> 00:14:17,950
One you started.

242
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:20,770
I know, but...

243
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:24,190
Well,

244
00:14:25,490 --> 00:14:27,060
you mentioned earlier...

245
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:30,310
Well...

246
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:33,610
Did you do something like this
with that guy back in college?

247
00:14:33,610 --> 00:14:34,310
What?

248
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:36,810
Ah.

249
00:14:37,460 --> 00:14:39,310
Actually, I'm not against

250
00:14:39,340 --> 00:14:41,000
doing these things with guys.

251
00:14:41,940 --> 00:14:43,670
Really?

252
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:50,470
Hey! What are you doing?

253
00:14:50,490 --> 00:14:51,540
Don't touch me!

254
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:53,520
Didn't you say you weren't against it?

255
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:54,950
I'm not, but...

256
00:14:55,420 --> 00:14:57,880
I know you stopped earlier.

257
00:14:58,350 --> 00:14:59,490
That's because...

258
00:14:59,510 --> 00:15:01,070
this is just too weird.

259
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,670
It's not fair.

260
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,710
Hey, Ryo!

261
00:15:04,740 --> 00:15:05,920
Wait!

262
00:15:23,220 --> 00:15:24,230
Okay.

263
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:26,360
I won.

264
00:15:35,940 --> 00:15:37,670
What on earth is going on today?

265
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:40,290
What a disaster.

266
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:43,640
I'm going home.

267
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:44,930
Hey!

268
00:15:47,770 --> 00:15:50,410
I haven't finished yet.

269
00:15:50,710 --> 00:15:53,520
What? Deal with that yourself...

270
00:15:54,540 --> 00:15:55,870
Hey, what are you doing?

271
00:15:56,660 --> 00:15:58,790
Since you've got experience with men,

272
00:15:59,000 --> 00:15:59,970
sleep with me.

273
00:15:59,990 --> 00:16:00,540
What?

274
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:02,240
How did it turn into this?

275
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:04,720
The winner calls the shots.

276
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:07,360
But...

277
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:14,340
In all the time I've known you,
this is a first.

278
00:16:14,340 --> 00:16:15,080
What?

279
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:18,810
You actually broke the rules
of our face-off.

280
00:16:21,900 --> 00:16:23,300
A real man keeps his word.

281
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:42,930
You okay?

282
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:45,590
Shut up.

283
00:18:46,340 --> 00:18:49,700
You're the one who got me like this,
and you still have the nerve to say that?

284
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:51,100
You're right.

285
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:57,800
If your body ends up needing me,

286
00:18:57,830 --> 00:18:59,160
I apologize in advance.

287
00:18:59,220 --> 00:19:00,310
That was my line.

288
00:19:00,980 --> 00:19:04,860
If you end up falling for me and can't be
with women anymore, don't blame me.

289
00:19:04,860 --> 00:19:05,670
What?

290
00:19:06,570 --> 00:19:09,050
You're the one who's going to fall for me.

291
00:19:11,270 --> 00:19:14,010
As if I'd ever fall for you.

292
00:19:14,970 --> 00:19:16,700
That's what I should be saying.

293
00:19:20,370 --> 00:19:21,120
Then...

294
00:19:22,710 --> 00:19:23,520
Shall we?

295
00:19:23,540 --> 00:19:24,230
What?

296
00:19:25,460 --> 00:19:27,260
Let's have a face-off over this.

297
00:19:29,860 --> 00:19:31,170
Gladly.

298
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:33,870
Then,

299
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:37,260
whoever makes the other
fall in love first wins.

300
00:19:41,110 --> 00:19:42,370
Deal.

301
00:19:52,430 --> 00:19:54,110
First to score wins.

302
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:56,580
Deal.

303
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:03,050
Oh!

304
00:20:03,380 --> 00:20:05,060
Come on!

305
00:20:05,090 --> 00:20:07,210
-I can't.
-I can't.

306
00:20:07,060 --> 00:20:10,490
[Exam Ranking List]

307
00:20:09,620 --> 00:20:11,830
Darn it.

308
00:20:11,850 --> 00:20:15,390
So, what should I make you do?

309
00:20:17,270 --> 00:20:18,340
I'm going home!

310
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:19,620
Hey, stick to the deal!

311
00:20:19,770 --> 00:20:22,280
See? Pretty impressive, right?

312
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:23,400
Impressive.

313
00:20:23,420 --> 00:20:24,580
Right?

314
00:20:25,070 --> 00:20:27,470
So heavy. Ugh, so heavy.

315
00:20:27,490 --> 00:20:28,390
You okay?

316
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,700
What was it again?

317
00:20:31,730 --> 00:20:33,510
Right.

318
00:20:37,550 --> 00:20:39,850
Yeah, this is it.

319
00:20:53,390 --> 00:20:55,480
That's the end of

320
00:20:56,510 --> 00:20:57,970
our cursed rivalry, then.

321
00:20:58,120 --> 00:21:00,590
Ah, what a relief.

322
00:21:05,250 --> 00:21:06,480
College life without me around

323
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:08,830
must be so dull for you.

324
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:10,680
Keep dreaming.

325
00:21:12,530 --> 00:21:13,370
Bye.

326
00:21:47,850 --> 00:21:48,590
Zen?

327
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:53,460
Ryo!

328
00:21:53,670 --> 00:21:56,200
It's really you. What are you doing here?

329
00:21:56,360 --> 00:21:57,310
What do you mean?

330
00:21:57,460 --> 00:21:59,790
Attending the new employee orientation.

331
00:22:01,220 --> 00:22:02,180
No way.

332
00:22:03,930 --> 00:22:05,460
You've got to be kidding me.

333
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,650
Ah... Then...

334
00:22:09,300 --> 00:22:11,700
Well... How about... we go again?

335
00:22:13,260 --> 00:22:14,270
Go again—what?

336
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:16,280
What do you mean, "what"?

337
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:17,640
A face-off.

338
00:22:22,570 --> 00:22:24,500
Whoever gets promoted first wins.

339
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:28,990
Deal.

340
00:23:01,160 --> 00:23:02,050
Morning.

341
00:23:03,750 --> 00:23:05,410
Want me to make you something?

342
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:07,450
Want some coffee?

343
00:23:08,340 --> 00:23:11,790
What? Okay.

344
00:23:16,710 --> 00:23:19,670
Ah... I almost forgot.

345
00:23:32,570 --> 00:23:33,370
Morning.

346
00:23:37,060 --> 00:23:40,660
What's with that look?

347
00:23:40,690 --> 00:23:43,650
It's already begun, hasn't it?
Our new face-off.

348
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:45,090
What?

349
00:23:45,120 --> 00:23:47,780
Whoever makes the other
fall in love first wins.

350
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:52,300
Don't tell me you're backing out now.

351
00:23:55,270 --> 00:23:56,510
As if.

352
00:23:56,910 --> 00:23:59,500
Also... I'll pass on the coffee.

353
00:24:14,390 --> 00:24:15,150
Bye.

354
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:28,470
Sorry.

355
00:25:32,450 --> 00:25:35,540
[In the Next Episode]

356
00:25:32,490 --> 00:25:34,950
How do you make someone
who's not interested in you

357
00:25:34,950 --> 00:25:36,110
fall for you?

358
00:25:35,560 --> 00:25:39,000
[Episode 2: Then I Won't Hold Back]

359
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:38,360
Oh, Yotsuya!

360
00:25:38,390 --> 00:25:40,610
Had fun yesterday, huh?

361
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:42,370
Want me to entertain you again?

362
00:25:43,810 --> 00:25:44,960
What do you think?

363
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:47,300
Suddenly asking me to come out—
what's wrong?

364
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:49,730
We've already spent a night together.

365
00:25:50,420 --> 00:25:51,900
Stop teasing me!

366
00:25:51,930 --> 00:25:54,590
How do you usually seduce men?

367
00:25:55,030 --> 00:25:57,360
That was your first time
with a man, right?

368
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:58,230
No.

369
00:25:58,250 --> 00:26:00,630
-What?
-You did it before?

370
00:26:00,660 --> 00:26:02,250
It was in high school.

